Lefferts Boulevard, west side, south of Jamaica Ave. (about 190 feet, right not shown). The Queens County Wheelmen's Club was still in existence in 1912 (people standing in front of club). The house to the right of the club was No. 277 in 1918.

About 1906.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Lefferts Boulevard, at the N.E. corner of Jamaica Avenue, the latter being on the extreme right with the subway "El" thereon. The building first appears on a 1909 map.

P. L. Sperr
August 22, 1932
